theorem Topology.isOpen_of_isClosed_of_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed A) (hP3 : Topology.P3 A) : IsOpen A := by
  have hsubset : A ⊆ interior (closure A) := hP3
  have hsubset' : A ⊆ interior A := by
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using hsubset
  have h_eq : interior A = A :=
    Set.Subset.antisymm interior_subset hsubset'
  simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior

theorem Topology.P3_iff_isOpen_of_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed A) : Topology.P3 A ↔ IsOpen A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP3
    -- From `P3` and the fact that `A` is closed, we obtain `A ⊆ interior A`.
    have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
      have h_closure : closure A = A := hA_closed.closure_eq
      have : A ⊆ interior (closure A) := hP3
      simpa [h_closure] using this
    -- Combining the inclusions gives `interior A = A`.
    have h_eq : (interior A : Set X) = A := by
      apply subset_antisymm
      · exact interior_subset
      · exact h_subset
    -- Hence `A` is open.
    simpa [h_eq] using isOpen_interior
  · intro hA_open
    exact Topology.P3_of_isOpen (A := A) hA_open

theorem Topology.closure_interior_eq_closure_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure (interior A) = closure A := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  ·
    exact closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
  ·
    have h₁ : A ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
    have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) := closure_mono h₁
    simpa [closure_closure] using h₂
